file-name: XC447057-adult male Black Redstart subsong Kennedy Quay Cork city 23rd December 2018_HH_1.mp3
rmk: More or less continuous subsong from an adult male before going to roost, incorporating a lot of mimicry. Species mimicked include Eurasian Wren, Blue Tit, Crested Tit, Tree Pipit, Dunnock, Common Chiffchaff. A few bursts of more typical, if subdued, Black Redstart song also included. High pass filter applied below 2kHz, but still a lot of background traffic noise from across the river.
